@node stpcpy
@section @code{stpcpy}---copy string returning a pointer to its end
@findex stpcpy
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <string.h>
char *stpcpy(char *restrict @var{dst}, const char *restrict @var{src});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
@code{stpcpy} copies the string pointed to by @var{src}
(including the terminating null character) to the array
pointed to by @var{dst}.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
This function returns a pointer to the end of the destination string,
thus pointing to the trailing '\0'.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{stpcpy} is a GNU extension, candidate for inclusion into POSIX/SUSv4.

@code{stpcpy} requires no supporting OS subroutines.

@*
